# /etc/default/astro-process on puppy.
# Stage 3 runs on puppy because that's where the frames physically live
# (the Pis write to puppy's NFS export). A Pi running its own stage 3 would
# read every frame back over NFS on a weak CPU — proven ~13x slower than
# puppy reading the same data locally (astrocam backfill, 2026-06-20). All
# cameras therefore set processing.host = "puppy"; the Pis keep stage 1
# (astro-state) + capture only. Revisit per-camera "self" only when a Pi
# gets its own local storage for its frames.
CAMERAS="--camera eclipticam-v1 --camera eclipticam-v3w --camera astrocam"
